
/*
 * The code snippet demonstrates the use of the [add] slot to append nodes to a destination node's children collection. It retrieves nodes specified by the [get-nodes] slot, which points to the children of the [type] node within the [.arguments] node, and adds them to the current node's children collection. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the current node's children collection.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes from the children of the [type] node within [.arguments].
 */
add:x:+
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/type
